data.description: Take a look at this Brooklyn Arts District gem!  3 bedroom, 1 bath, very nicely updated home, including granite counter tops, LVP flooring, stainless steel appliances and more. From the covered front porch, you enter into a cozy living room with spacious, open kitchen and dining just down the hall.  Kitchen pantry, large numerous closets, and even a mudroom are features you don't often find in this size home, making it feel and live bigger than the square footage indicates.  This property includes the adjoining lot at 819 Hanover Street which allows for generous off-street parking.  That, and the private fenced side yard with storage shed, makes this even more of a downtown find.   Location is so convenient with easy walk to the Wilmington Riverfront, numerous restaurants, and only 8 miles to Wrightsville Beach.  New HVAC December 2022 and crawl space encapsulated in 2021, so no worries there!
